sentences.chinese: 腕龍的行爲舉止是什麼樣？

sentences.english: The Brachiosaurus' front legs were longer than its back legs.
The Brachiosaurus was a plant eater. It ate tops of tall trees.
sentences.chinese: 腕龍是草食動物，它喫樹梢處的葉子。

sentences.english: Brachiosaurus did not take care of their babies.
sentences.chinese: 腕龍不照看自己的孩子。

sentences.english: The Brachiosaurus was one of the tallest and largest dinosaurs.
sentences.chinese: 腕龍是最高最大的恐龍之一。

sentences.english: Brachiosaurus is definitely the star of the show.
sentences.chinese: 腕龍絕對是這場秀中的明星。

sentences.english: Its nostrils were on the top of its head.
sentences.chinese: 腕龍的鼻孔長在頭頂上。

sentences.english: It did not chew, it swallowed the food whole. Large meat eating dinosaurs killed Brachiosaurus to eat it.
sentences.chinese: 喫東西時，腕龍不咀嚼就將食物整塊吞下。

sentences.english: The Brachiosaurus had a very small brain and was not smart.
sentences.chinese: 腕龍有個非常小的腦袋，因此不太聰明。
